<keyStep id="00702E08C323731E94D8FF2665E6FECF" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<paragraph id="BB3B36ADC323731E94D8FF2665E6FE84" blockId="3.[151,1437,213,323]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<keyLead id="00759598C323731E94D8FF2665E6FE84" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">1. Lateral receptacles of the spermathecae extend further forward than the median receptacles and are further apart than the atria and surrounding sclerotised areas........................................................................ 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB3B36ADC323731E94D2FEE165E6FECF" blockId="3.[151,1437,213,323]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<keyLead id="00759598C323731E94D2FEE165E6FECF" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">– Lateral receptacles of the spermathecae extend no more than a little further forward than the median receptacles and are not further apart than the atria.............................................................................. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="00702E08C323731E94D8FE9865E7FE5A" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<paragraph id="BB3B36ADC323731E94D8FE9865E6FE10" blockId="3.[151,1437,360,470]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<keyLead id="00759598C323731E94D8FE9865E6FE10" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
2. Strong lateral stripes on the dorsal abdomen; a moustache-shaped marking in the middle of the dorsal abdomen; palp mid brown with off-white metatarsus; thick connection between spermathecal receptacles............... 
<taxonomicName id="7C844D2EC323731E90C0FE766560FE16" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="2022" box="[1167,1306,389,411]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Papuaneon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurobodalla">
<emphasis id="89F0EABFC323731E90C0FE766560FE16" box="[1167,1306,389,411]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">P. eurobodalla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
