</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BB3B36ADC323731E94D2FC2A65E6FB80" blockId="3.[151,1437,956,1037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<keyLead id="00759598C323731E94D2FC2A65E6FB80" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">– bulb of embolus clearly distal to the tegular shelf, tibial apophysis not short, pointed and aimed directly away from the tibia (either almost absent or pointing distally); with a sparse, grey clypeal fringe...................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
